description: From Late Latin domābilis (“tameable”), from domāre (“to tame”), present infinitive of domō (“to break in, to tame”), from Proto-Italic *domaō (“to tame”), from Proto-Indo-European *demh₂- (“to domesticate, to tame”); compare Old French domable.

adjectives.description: domable (comparative more domable, superlative most domable)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, rare) Capable of being tamed; tameable, domesticable.
